al and technological wellbeing through movement, making, and repair.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aAutomobilesxSocial aspectszTanzania. 0aAutomobileszTanzaniaxHistoryy20th century. 0aEconomic developmentxSocial aspectszTanzania. 0aTechnologyxSocial aspectszTanzania. 7aHISTORY / Africa / East.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478021278zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021278423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021278/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles